# Styling & Party Theme

## Theme Colors (defined in globals.css)

Custom party colors available as Tailwind classes:
- `text-party-pink`, `bg-party-pink` ‚Äî vibrant pink
- `text-party-purple`, `bg-party-purple` ‚Äî deep purple (also `--primary`)
- `text-party-orange`, `bg-party-orange` ‚Äî warm orange
- `text-party-yellow`, `bg-party-yellow` ‚Äî bright yellow
- `text-party-green`, `bg-party-green` ‚Äî fresh green
- `text-party-blue`, `bg-party-blue` ‚Äî sky blue

## Gradient Utilities

- `.party-gradient` ‚Äî full vibrant gradient (pink ‚Üí purple ‚Üí blue ‚Üí green) for CTAs and icons
- `.party-gradient-soft` ‚Äî muted version for backgrounds

## Typography

- `font-heading` (Poppins) ‚Äî headings, titles, emphasis, CTAs
- `font-sans` (Inter) ‚Äî body text, inherited by default
- Heading sizes: `text-4xl` / `text-3xl` for page titles, `text-2xl` / `text-xl` for section headings, `text-lg` for card titles

## Spacing Scale

Consistent spacing keeps the UI harmonious:
- **Component internal padding**: `p-4` (cards), `p-6` (dialogs/sections)
- **Stack spacing**: `space-y-4` for form fields, `space-y-6` for page sections, `space-y-8` for major blocks
- **Grid/flex gaps**: `gap-4` for card grids, `gap-6` for dashboard layouts
- **Page margins**: `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8` for responsive horizontal padding
- Prefer `gap-*` on flex/grid containers over `space-y-*` / `space-x-*` when possible

## Responsive Breakpoints

Mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints:
- Default (< 640px) ‚Äî single column, stacked layouts, full-width cards
- `sm:` (640px) ‚Äî two-column grids where appropriate
- `md:` (768px) ‚Äî sidebar layouts, wider form fields
- `lg:` (1024px) ‚Äî max-width containers, three-column grids
- `xl:` (1280px) ‚Äî used sparingly, mainly for max-width constraints

Invite template pages should be fully responsive ‚Äî test at 375px, 768px, and 1440px.

## Animation Conventions (Framer Motion)

### Page Transitions
```tsx
const pageVariants = {
  initial: { opacity: 0, y: 20 },
  animate: { opacity: 1, y: 0 },
  exit: { opacity: 0, y: -10 },
};
// transition: { duration: 0.3, ease: "easeOut" }
```

### Component Entrance (cards, list items)
```tsx
const cardVariants = {
  initial: { opacity: 0, scale: 0.95 },
  animate: { opacity: 1, scale: 1 },
};
// Use staggerChildren: 0.05 on parent for list stagger
```

### Interactive Elements (hover, tap)
```tsx
<motion.div whileHover={{ scale: 1.02 }} whileTap={{ scale: 0.98 }}>
```

Rules:
- Prefer `transform` and `opacity` animations ‚Äî never animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`
- Keep durations short: 0.2s‚Äì0.4s for UI, up to 0.6s for page transitions
- Use `AnimatePresence` for mount/unmount animations
- Template decorative animations (confetti, hearts, stars) can be longer (1‚Äì3s) with loops

## Dark Mode

The project uses `next-themes` with CSS variables. When adding new custom colors or backgrounds:
- Define both light and dark values in `globals.css` using `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark)` or the `.dark` class
- Use the semantic tokens (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--card`, `--primary`) rather than hardcoded hex values
- Test both themes when modifying any visible UI

## General Conventions

- Use `rounded-2xl` or `rounded-full` for the playful party feel
- Primary CTA buttons: `party-gradient text-white font-semibold`
- Cards: shadcn `Card` with `hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all`
- Use `motion.div` for entrance animations on pages and major sections
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional class merging ‚Äî never string concatenation
